commentPostTextItems.html: We have just lost the broadcast for the game but hope to get things back on track as soon as possible. Please bear with us.
The broadcast has been interrupted due to a power failure at the venue

The broadcast has not yet been restored, but we have news from Harare that Zimbabwe have been bowled out for 146, with Ajantha Mendis finishing with figures of 6 for 29 in nine overs. Thushara finished with 2 for 13, and Mubarak and Prasad captured one each.
Keith Dabengwa top-scored for Zimbabwe with 36. The hosts failed to measure up to Mendis' spin yet again, losing nine wickets for 80 runs.
The players are taking lunch, the broadcast has resumed, and we'll be back as soon as the Sri Lanka come out to bat. They shouldn't take too long to finish this off.
Apologies again for the loss of commentary, and thanks for your patience
